<subSubSection id="9E82650CFFBAFFB0E399FF5BFEF54E8A" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D6273687FFBAFFB0E399FF5BFBF84E1A" blockId="11.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBAFFB0E399FF5BFE794FC7" bold="true" box="[189,492,194,220]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBAFFB0E134FF5AFC8A4FC7" authorityName="Gottschl. &amp; S. Orsenigo" authorityYear="2021" box="[528,799,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scopolioides">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBAFFB0E134FF5AFC8A4FC7" box="[528,799,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Hieracium scopolioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known only from the grasslands above the treeline of Mount Lesima. It grows on meadows at elevations between 1550 and 
<quantity id="11609B62FFBAFFB0E735FF7FFBFC4E1A" box="[1041,1129,230,257]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" unit="m" value="1650.0">1650 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D6273687FFBAFFB0E399FE93FEF54E8A" blockId="11.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBAFFB0E399FE93FE3C4E3F" bold="true" box="[189,425,266,292]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Conservation status</emphasis>
:—Due to its restricted range and reduced number of mature individuals (&lt;1,000), 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBAFFB0E610FE92FE814E53" authorityName="Gottschl. &amp; S. Orsenigo" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scopolioides">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBAFFB0E610FE92FE814E53" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Hieracium scopolioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could preliminary be listed as “Vulnerable” (VU) under criterion D1, according to the IUCN criteria (2019). Despite at the moment there are no ongoing threats, changes in grazing pressure could have a negative impact on 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBAFFB0E38FFEEEFECC4E8B" authorityName="Gottschl. &amp; S. Orsenigo" authorityYear="2021" box="[171,345,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scopolioides">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBAFFB0E38FFEEEFECC4E8B" box="[171,345,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">H. scopolioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9E82650CFFBAFFB0E399FE03FB344D5F" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D6273687FFBAFFB0E399FE03FB344D5F" blockId="11.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBAFFB0E399FE03FEBF4EAF" bold="true" box="[189,298,410,436]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Remarks</emphasis>
:—In its habit 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBAFFB0E2F4FE02FDEA4EAF" authorityName="Gottschl. &amp; S. Orsenigo" authorityYear="2021" box="[464,639,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scopolioides">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBAFFB0E2F4FE02FDEA4EAF" box="[464,639,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">H. scopolioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBAFFB0E1DBFE02FCEE4EAF" authorityName="Gottschl. &amp; S. Orsenigo" authorityYear="2021" box="[767,891,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scopolii">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBAFFB0E1DBFE02FCEE4EAF" box="[767,891,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">H. scopolii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the same locality, but differs by developing an indistinct basal rosette, the more entire leaves and the long glandular hairs on peduncles and phyllaries. In these characters it resembles 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBAFFB0E2BCFE7AFCFE4EE7" authority="Gottschlich (2009: 179)" authorityName="Gottschlich" authorityPageNumber="179" authorityYear="2009" box="[408,875,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="umbrosoides">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBAFFB0E2BCFE7AFDD94EE7" box="[408,588,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">H. umbrosoides</emphasis>
Gottschlich (2009: 179)
</taxonomicName>
, occurring in the same region. Thus, it may have originally evolved from these two species. Currently it is more frequent on M. Lesima than 
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBAFFB0E783FD9EFE814D5F" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBAFFB0E783FD9EFAB24D3B" authorityName="Gottschl. &amp; S. Orsenigo" authorityYear="2021" box="[1191,1319,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scopolii">H. scopolii</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBAFFB0E610FD9EFE814D5F" authorityName="Gottschl. &amp; S. Orsenigo" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hieracium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scopolioides">Hieracium scopolioides</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
should be classified in 
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBAFFB0E138FDB2FDA24D5F" box="[540,567,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">H.</emphasis>
sect. 
<taxonomicName id="11984D04FFBAFFB0E153FDB3FC3A4D5F" authority="Stace &amp; P. D. Sell" authorityName="Stace &amp; P. D. Sell" box="[631,943,554,581]" class="Cnidaria (awaiting allocation)" family="Cnidaria (awaiting allocation)" genus="Umbrosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cnidaria (awaiting allocation)" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E4ECEA95FFBAFFB0E153FDB3FD4B4D5F" box="[631,734,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Umbrosa</emphasis>
Stace &amp; P. D. Sell
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="B2094B76FFBAFFB0E0F6FDB3FB094D5F" author="Stace, C. A." box="[978,1180,554,580]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" pagination="417 - 441" refId="ref8694" refString="Stace, C. A. (1998) Sectional names in the genus Hieracium (Asteraceae) sensu stricto. Edinburgh Journal of Botany 55 (3): 417 - 441. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0960428600003279" type="journal article" year="1998">Stace (1998: 438)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
